.TH LINUX-HELLO-DAEMON 8 "18 December 2025" "linux-hello 1.0.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
linux-hello-daemon \- Linux facial authentication system background service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B linux-hello-daemon
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B linux-hello-daemon
is the background service component of the Linux Hello facial authentication system.
It runs as a systemd service and manages face recognition requests, maintains the Unix socket
for IPC (Inter-Process Communication), and handles daemon operations.
.PP
The daemon:
.RS
.IP \- 2
Listens on Unix socket `/run/linux-hello.sock` for authentication requests
.IP \-
Manages face embeddings and recognition operations
.IP \-
Coordinates with PAM authentication modules
.IP \-
Provides system-wide facial recognition services
.IP \-
Logs operations to systemd journal
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show program version and exit.
.SH SYSTEMD INTEGRATION
The daemon is managed by systemd and can be controlled via:
.TP
Start the daemon:
.B sudo systemctl start linux-hello
.TP
Stop the daemon:
.B sudo systemctl stop linux-hello
.TP
Restart the daemon:
.B sudo systemctl restart linux-hello
.TP
Enable on boot:
.B sudo systemctl enable linux-hello
.TP
Disable from boot:
.B sudo systemctl disable linux-hello
.TP
Check status:
.B systemctl status linux-hello
.TP
View service logs:
.B journalctl -u linux-hello -f
.SH SOCKET
The daemon communicates via Unix domain socket:
.B /run/linux-hello.sock
.PP
This socket is used for IPC between:
.RS
.IP \- 2
CLI interface (`hello` command)
.IP \-
PAM authentication module
.IP \-
System authentication framework
.RE
.PP
Socket permissions:
.B 0666 (rw-rw-rw-)
allowing all users to connect for authentication requests.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The daemon reads configuration from:
.B /etc/linux-hello/config.json
.PP
Configuration includes:
.RS
.IP \- 2
Default camera selection
.IP \-
Recognition thresholds
.IP \-
Logging settings
.RE
.SH DATABASE
Face embeddings are stored in:
.B /var/lib/linux-hello/faces/
.PP
Data structure:
.RS
.IP \- 2
`USERNAME/embedding.npy` - Face embedding vectors (NumPy format)
.IP \-
`USERNAME/metadata.json` - User metadata and registration info
.RE
.PP
Directory permissions:
.B 0700 (rwx------)
restricting access to root only.
.SH LOGGING
All daemon operations are logged to systemd journal:
.PP
View all logs:
.B journalctl -u linux-hello
.PP
View recent logs in real-time:
.B journalctl -u linux-hello -f
.PP
Filter by priority:
.B journalctl -u linux-hello -p err
.PP
View logs for a time range:
.B journalctl -u linux-hello --since "1 hour ago"
.SH SIGNALS
The daemon responds to standard signals:
.TP
.B SIGTERM
Graceful shutdown
.TP
.B SIGINT
Immediate shutdown
.TP
.B SIGHUP
Reload configuration (not implemented)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful operation
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 2
Initialization error (socket, config, etc.)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hello (1),
.BR pam_linux_hello (8),
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR journalctl (1),
.BR unix (7)
